# Plan: Add `@ai-sdk/pixelart` Provider Package

## Context

The Vercel AI SDK uses a modular provider pattern where each AI service is an independent package under `packages/<provider>`. A new fictional "PixelArt" provider needs to be added that exclusively supports image generation (no text/chat/embeddings/speech/video). It exposes a `createPixelArt` factory function and accepts image-specific settings for `size`, `style` ("pixel" | "retro" | "8bit"), and `pixelDensity`. The base URL is `https://api.pixelart.ai/v1`.

**Reference implementations studied:**
- `packages/fal/` — image-only-focused provider (closest analog)
- `packages/openai/` — multi-capability provider with image support

---

## Files to Create

```
packages/pixelart/
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── tsconfig.build.json
├── tsup.config.ts
├── turbo.json
├── vitest.node.config.js
├── vitest.edge.config.js
├── README.md
├── CHANGELOG.md
└── src/
    ├── index.ts
    ├── version.ts
    ├── pixelart-provider.ts
    ├── pixelart-provider.test.ts
    ├── pixelart-image-model.ts
    ├── pixelart-image-model.test.ts
    ├── pixelart-image-settings.ts
    └── pixelart-image-options.ts
```

## File to Modify

- `tsconfig.json` (root) — add `{ "path": "packages/pixelart" }` between `perplexity` and `provider` entries

---

