# AI SDK - PixelArt Provider

The **PixelArt provider** for the [AI SDK](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs) enables image generation with pixel-art aesthetics via the [PixelArt API](https://api.pixelart.ai/v1).

> **Note:** PixelArt is an image-generation-only provider. It does not support text generation, embeddings, speech synthesis, or any other modality.

## Setup

```bash
npm i @ai-sdk/pixelart
```

## Provider Instance

You can import the default provider instance `pixelart` or create a custom instance with `createPixelArt`:

```ts
import { pixelart } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
// or
import { createPixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';

const pixelart = createPixelArt({
  apiKey: 'your-api-key', // defaults to process.env.PIXELART_API_KEY
});
```

## Image Generation

```ts
import { pixelart } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
import { generateImage } from 'ai';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelart.image('pixelart-standard-v1'),
  prompt: 'A brave knight standing in a medieval pixel art village',
});
```

### Provider-Specific Options

Pass PixelArt-specific settings via `providerOptions.pixelart`:

```ts
import { pixelart } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
import { generateImage } from 'ai';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelart.image('pixelart-hd-v1'),
  prompt: 'A neon-lit city street at night',
  size: '512x512',
  providerOptions: {
    pixelart: {
      style: 'retro',      // 'pixel' | 'retro' | '8bit'
      pixelDensity: 8,     // 1–16, controls pixel grid density
    },
  },
});
```

#### Available `style` values

| Value    | Description                                   |
| -------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `pixel`  | Classic pixel art style (default)             |
| `retro`  | Retro-inspired aesthetic with limited palette |
| `8bit`   | 8-bit video game aesthetic                    |

#### `pixelDensity`

A number between `1` and `16` controlling how coarse the pixel grid is. Higher values produce finer detail.

## Available Models

| Model ID                | Description                        |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `pixelart-standard-v1`  | Standard resolution pixel art      |
| `pixelart-hd-v1`        | High-definition pixel art output   |

## Authentication

Set the `PIXELART_API_KEY` environment variable or pass `apiKey` to `createPixelArt`:

```bash
PIXELART_API_KEY=your-key-here
```

## Documentation

For full API documentation, visit [https://ai-sdk.dev/docs](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs).

